# Slack Automation

## Message Formatting
- Use Markdown: `*bold*`, `_italic_`, `~strikethrough~`
- Code: \`inline\` or \`\`\`block\`\`\`
- Mentions: `<@USER_ID>` (not @username)
- Channels: `<#CHANNEL_ID>`
- Links: `<URL|display text>`

## Common Patterns

### Send Message to Channel
1. Find channel ID (not name)
2. Send with `markdown_text` parameter
3. Save `channel` and `message.ts` for edits/threads

### Thread Replies
- Use `thread_ts` from parent message
- Without `thread_ts`, message posts to main channel

### Reactions
- Emoji names without colons: `thumbsup`, `wave`
- Custom emojis: `name:id` format

## Search Modifiers
- `in:#channel` - Search in specific channel
- `from:@user` - From specific user
- `has:link` - Messages with links
- `before:YYYY-MM-DD` / `after:YYYY-MM-DD` - Date range
- `has:file` - Messages with attachments

## Best Practices
- Keep messages concise and scannable
- Use threads for discussions
- React instead of "+1" messages
- Use code blocks for technical content
- Schedule important messages for optimal timing
